Privacy Policy
Effective Date: February 4, 2026
Revise.[ (“we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting your personal information. This Privacy Policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and your rights regarding your data.
1. Information We Collect
We collect the following information to provide and improve our services:
Account Information
Email address – used for creating an account, logging in, and sharing content.
User-Generated Content
Flashcards, notes, to-do lists, or other content you create in the app.
Stored securely so you can access it later or share it if you choose.
Usage Data
Metrics such as completed flashcards, timers, and box breathing exercises.
Helps us improve app functionality and user experience.
Subscription Information
Your subscription status (active, canceled, etc.) is tracked to provide access to paid features.
Subscription payments are securely processed by RevenueCat, Apple, or Google. We do not store or access your payment information.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Facilitate account creation and authentication
Store and manage your content
Track progress and app usage
Manage subscription access
Enable sharing features if you choose
Communicate important updates or account notices
We do not sell or trade your personal information.
3. How We Store Your Information
All personal information, user-generated content, usage data, and subscription status are stored securely in Supabase / our backend.
We implement technical and organizational security measures to protect your data.
4. Sharing Your Information
We may share your information only:
With service providers who help us operate the app (e.g., Supabase, RevenueCat)
When required by law or to protect our rights
We do not sell or share your personal information for marketing purposes.
5. Data Retention
We retain your data as long as your account exists.
If you delete your account or request data deletion, we will remove your data from active systems and anonymize backups.
6. Privacy of Minors
Our app is intended for users aged 13 and above.
Users under 18 should obtain parental or guardian consent before using the app.
We do not knowingly collect information from children under 13.
If we learn that a child under 13 has provided personal information, we will delete it promptly.
Parents or guardians may contact us at [your email address] to request deletion of a child’s data.
7. Your Privacy Rights
Depending on your location, you may have the right to:
Access your personal data
Correct or update your data
Delete your account and associated data
Withdraw consent for data processing
Restrict certain processing or request portability
To exercise these rights, contact us at: [your email address]
8. Subscription and Payment Information
Subscriptions are managed through RevenueCat, Apple, or Google Play.
We do not handle credit card or payment information.
For billing questions or refunds, contact RevenueCat or the respective app store.
9. Updates to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to stay compliant with laws or improve clarity.
Material changes will be communicated in the app or via email.
Please review this policy regularly.
10. Contact Us
If you have questions about this Privacy Policy or your data, contact us at:
Email: study.inc.dev@gmail.com
